T1  - The Impact of Community Violence and an Organization's Procedural Justice Climate on Workplace Aggression
AU  - Dietz, Joerg
AU  - Robinson, Sandra L.
AU  - Folger, Robert
AU  - Baron, Robert A.
AU  - Schulz, Martin
Y1  - 2003/06/01
PY  - 2003
DA  - 2003/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/30040625
DO  - 10.5465/30040625
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 317
EP  - 326
VL  - 46
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This study contrasts community violence and an organization's procedural justice climate (or lack thereof) as explanations for employee-instigated workplace aggression in the geographically dispersed plants of a nationwide organization. The findings showed that violent crime rates in the community where a plant resided predicted workplace aggression in that plant, whereas the plant's procedural justice climate did not.
AB  - This study contrasts community violence and an organization's procedural justice climate (or lack thereof) as explanations for employee-instigated workplace aggression in the geographically dispersed plants of a nationwide organization. The findings showed that violent crime rates in the community where a plant resided predicted workplace aggression in that plant, whereas the plant's procedural justice climate did not.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/30040625
