T1  - A Social Capital Model of High-Growth Ventures
AU  - Florin, Juan
AU  - Lubatkin, Michael
AU  - Schulze, William
Y1  - 2003/06/01
PY  - 2003
DA  - 2003/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/30040630
DO  - 10.5465/30040630
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 374
EP  - 384
VL  - 46
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - We Use social capital theory to explain how human and social capital affect a venture's ability to accumulate financial capital during its growth stages (before an initial public offering) and its performance during the two-year period after going public. Consistent with theory, data drawn from a sample of 275 ventures that went public indicate that social capital leverages the productivity of a venture's resource base and provides the venture with a durable source of competitive advantage.
AB  - We Use social capital theory to explain how human and social capital affect a venture's ability to accumulate financial capital during its growth stages (before an initial public offering) and its performance during the two-year period after going public. Consistent with theory, data drawn from a sample of 275 ventures that went public indicate that social capital leverages the productivity of a venture's resource base and provides the venture with a durable source of competitive advantage.
